#encoding: utf-8

Feature: Match3 - Match fixed length patterns

  Scenario: [1] Get neighbours
    Given an empty graph
    And having executed:
      """
      CREATE (a:A {num: 1})-[:KNOWS]->(b:B {num: 2})
      """
    When executing query:
      """
      MATCH (n1)-[rel:KNOWS]->(n2)
      RETURN n1, n2
      """
    Then the result should be, in any order:
      | n1            | n2            |
      | (:A {num: 1}) | (:B {num: 2}) |
    And no side effects

